article.headline: Jacksonville 82, Fla Atlantic 81
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- David Lee scored 23 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer with four seconds to play, to give Jacksonville an 82-81 win over Florida Atlantic on Tuesday night. Jacksonville (6-7, 2-4 Atlantic Sun Conference) trailed 81-73 with 1:20 remaining before Lee reeled off three straight 3-pointers to end the game. Lee's first two 3-pointers cut the deficit to 81-79 with 35 seconds left before Aubrey Conerly stole Tywain McTyer's pass to set up the final shot. Antonio Cool missed a potential game-winning shot, but the Dolphins got the ball out of bounds and Jesse Kimbrough found Lee in the corner for the game winner. Haminn Quaintance stole the ensuing inbounds pass to preserve the win. Quaintance also added 18 points for the Dolphins, who also got 14 points from Kimbrough and 12 from Cool. Mike Bell led Florida Atlantic (3-10, 3-3) with 24 points, while Robert Williams scored a season-high 15. Webb added 12 points for the Owls while McTyer added 11. FAU held a 40-32 halftime lead and extended the lead to as much as 13. The Owls later led 75-65 with 5:22 left, but the Dolphins closed the game on a 17-6 run.
